=== K0 of a projective bundle ===
Another important formula for the Grothendieck group is the projective bundle formula: given a rank r vector bundle formula_101 over a Noetherian scheme formula_46, the Grothendieck group of the projective bundle formula_103 is a free formula_93-module of rank &quot;r&quot; with basis formula_105. This formula allows one to compute the Grothendieck group of formula_106. This make it possible to compute the formula_107 or Hirzebruch surfaces. In addition, this can be used to compute the Grothendieck group formula_89 by observing it is a projective bundle over the field formula_81.

=== K0 of singular spaces and spaces with isolated quotient singularities ===
One recent technique for computing the Grothendieck group of spaces with minor singularities comes from evaluating the difference between formula_55 and formula_73, which comes from the fact every vector bundle can be equivalently described as a coherent sheaf. This is done using the Grothendieck group of the Singularity category formula_112 from derived noncommutative algebraic geometry. It gives a long exact sequence starting with
